The triple and emphatic repetition of the word ‘Credo’ introducing the statement of belief in each separate person of the Holy Trinity is a remarkable feature in the Bangor Creed.

Credo in Deum Patrem. Credo et in Jesum Christum. Credo et in Spiritum Sanctum. Two more Credos are added toward the end Credo vitam post mortem. Haec omnia credo in Deum. Amen.

The separate ‘Credo’ for each Person in the Holy Trinity is found in the Baptismal Creed in the Sacro- mentan'um Gallicanum. The two further additions of ‘Credo' at the close find no parallel either there or, so far as we know, elsewhere.
